[
    {
        "content": "<p>Hi all, I'm bumping into a bit of a bizarre error. This is my first time using b4 to fetch patches. I'm currently looking at this patch set: <a href=\"https://lore.kernel.org/lkml/ZJm%2FJfIPMrgXkYpp@boqun-archlinux/T/\">https://lore.kernel.org/lkml/ZJm%2FJfIPMrgXkYpp@boqun-archlinux/T/</a>. I'm running the command</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Rust\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"n\">b4</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">shazam</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">ZJm</span><span class=\"o\">%</span><span class=\"mi\">2</span><span class=\"n\">FJfIPMrgXkYpp</span><span class=\"o\">@</span><span class=\"n\">boqun</span><span class=\"o\">-</span><span class=\"n\">archlinux</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>and get the error message</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Rust\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"n\">Grabbing</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">thread</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">from</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">lore</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"n\">kernel</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"n\">org</span><span class=\"o\">/</span><span class=\"n\">all</span><span class=\"o\">/</span><span class=\"n\">ZJm</span><span class=\"o\">%</span><span class=\"mi\">252</span><span class=\"n\">FJfIPMrgXkYpp</span><span class=\"o\">@</span><span class=\"n\">boqun</span><span class=\"o\">-</span><span class=\"n\">archlinux</span><span class=\"o\">/</span><span class=\"n\">t</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"n\">mbox</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"n\">gz</span>\n<span class=\"n\">That</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">message</span><span class=\"o\">-</span><span class=\"n\">id</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">is</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">not</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">known</span><span class=\"p\">.</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>Am I doing something obviously wrong in b4?</p>",
        "id": 443822018,
        "sender_full_name": "John Baublitz",
        "timestamp": 1718040052
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>maybe it doesn't work because you need to unquote the <code>%</code>? Anyway, since the cover-letter of the patch is really:</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://lore.kernel.org/lkml/20230625121657.3631109-1-changxian.cqs@antgroup.com/\">[RFC PATCH 0/8] Rust device mapper abstractions - Qingsong Chen (kernel.org)</a></p>\n<p>you could try</p>\n<p><code>b4 shazam 20230625121657.3631109-1-changxian.cqs@antgroup.com</code></p>",
        "id": 443822459,
        "sender_full_name": "Boqun Feng",
        "timestamp": 1718040221
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>It looks like the message-id has a / in it, which is being URL-encoded to %2F: try <code>b4 shazam \"ZJm/JfIPMrgXkYpp@boqun-archlinux\"</code></p>",
        "id": 443822461,
        "sender_full_name": "Jeremy Cline",
        "timestamp": 1718040222
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span class=\"user-mention silent\" data-user-id=\"411647\">Boqun Feng</span> <a href=\"#narrow/stream/291565-Help/topic/b4.20error.20on.20LKML.20patch.20fetch/near/443822459\">said</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p><code>b4 shazam 20230625121657.3631109-1-changxian.cqs@antgroup.com</code></p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>Okay this worked, thanks! Sorry for the noise.</p>",
        "id": 443823121,
        "sender_full_name": "John Baublitz",
        "timestamp": 1718040447
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>No worries, now you only need to help 3 more people on this as in <em>Pay It Forward</em></p>",
